# Benchmark Source Implementation Flow

This is the implementation plan for the improved benchmark system.

---

## Build Order

Do this in order:

```text
1. Shared normalized benchmark definition types
2. Source adapter types
3. Validator
4. Built-in definition loader
5. Local JSON adapter
6. Local CSV adapter
7. Install/cache system
8. Registry
9. Progress-only fallback
10. Tests
11. Settings UI model
12. GitHub/Google Sheet adapters later
```

Do not start with UI.

---

## 1. Shared Types

Create:

```text
src/engine/benchmarks/shared/NormalizedBenchmarkDefinition.ts
```

Types:
- NormalizedBenchmarkDefinition
- BenchmarkScenarioDefinition
- BenchmarkRankDefinition
- BenchmarkThresholdDefinition
- BenchmarkCategoryDefinition
- BenchmarkSourceMetadata
- BenchmarkValidationResult
- PlatformId
- UniversalAimCategory
- ScoringDirection

---

## 2. Source Adapter Types

Create:

```text
src/engine/benchmarks/sources/BenchmarkSourceAdapter.ts
```

Types:

```ts
export type BenchmarkSourceType =
  | "built-in"
  | "local-json"
  | "local-csv"
  | "google-sheet-csv"
  | "github-raw-json"
  | "github-raw-csv"
  | "custom-created";

export type BenchmarkSourceInput = {
  type: BenchmarkSourceType;
  path?: string;
  url?: string;
  mappingPreset?: string;
};

export type BenchmarkSourceImportResult =
  | {
      ok: true;
      definition: NormalizedBenchmarkDefinition;
      warnings: string[];
    }
  | {
      ok: false;
      errors: string[];
      warnings: string[];
    };

export type BenchmarkSourceAdapter = {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  supportedTypes: BenchmarkSourceType[];
  canHandle(input: BenchmarkSourceInput): boolean;
  importSource(input: BenchmarkSourceInput): Promise<BenchmarkSourceImportResult>;
};
```

---

## 3. Validator

Create:

```text
src/engine/benchmarks/shared/validateBenchmarkDefinition.ts
```

Validation checks:
- definition has id/name/version
- scenario IDs unique
- rank IDs unique
- thresholds reference existing scenarios
- thresholds reference existing ranks
- every scenario has platform
- every scenario has native category
- every scenario has universal category
- universal categories are valid
- scoring direction valid
- threshold scores are numbers
- aliases do not conflict inside same definition

Invalid definitions should not crash the app.

Return clear errors.

---

## 4. Built-In Definition Loader

Create:

```text
src/engine/benchmarks/sources/builtInDefinitionLoader.ts
```

It loads bundled definitions from:

```text
src/engine/benchmarks/builtin/
  voltaic/
    definition.json
  viscose/
    definition.json
```

The loader should validate built-in definitions in tests.

