## 7. Install / Cache System

Create:

```text
src/engine/benchmarks/install/installBenchmarkDefinition.ts
```

Install flow:

```text
source adapter import
↓
validation
↓
preview
↓
user confirms
↓
copy/cache normalized definition locally
↓
store settings metadata
↓
registry refresh
```

---

## 8. Registry

Create:

```text
src/engine/benchmarks/registry/benchmarkDefinitionRegistry.ts
```

Responsibilities:
- list installed definitions
- get active definition
- enable/disable definitions
- prevent duplicate active IDs
- handle built-in and user-installed definitions
- expose benchmark-agnostic summaries to UI

---

## 9. Database Table

Add:

```sql
CREATE TABLE benchmark_definition_settings (
  definition_id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  version TEXT NOT NULL,
  source_type TEXT NOT NULL,
  source_name TEXT,
  source_url TEXT,
  installed_path TEXT,
  enabled INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,
  installed_at TEXT NOT NULL,
  last_checked_at TEXT,
  last_validated_at TEXT,
  validation_status TEXT NOT NULL,
  is_official_data INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0
);
```

---

## 10. Settings UI Model

The Settings UI should show:

```text
Benchmark Sources / Definitions
- Voltaic       Built-in       Enabled
- Viscose       Built-in       Enabled
- My Benchmark  Local CSV      Disabled

Actions:
- Import JSON
- Import CSV
- Add source URL later
- Enable/Disable
- View details
- Validate again
- Remove user-installed definition
```

Built-in definitions can be disabled but not removed.

---

## 11. Engine Integration

The engine flow:

```text
raw runs
↓
active benchmark definition
↓
scenario matching using names/aliases
↓
threshold lookup if available
↓
rank progress or progress-only
↓
universal category analysis
↓
weakness detection
↓
recommendation
↓
coach summary
```

Engine functions should accept a normalized definition:

```ts
analyzeRuns({ runs, benchmarkDefinition })
```

Do not hardcode Voltaic.

---

## 12. Tests

Required tests:
- built-in definition validates
- local JSON imports valid definition
- invalid JSON fails clearly
- CSV adapter creates valid definition
- missing thresholds use progress-only
- same engine analyzes Voltaic and Viscose sample definitions
- UI-facing analysis object does not include source-specific weirdness
- user-installed definition can be enabled/disabled

